Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.12,0:09:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to ProSeka AfterTalk for the event "Reaching Out to an Unraveling Tomorrow."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.46,0:09:42.60,Default,host,0,0,0,,Yay!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.40,0:09:44.48,Default,host,0,0,0,,Good evening, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.48,0:09:48.40,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'm Hinata Sato, the voice of Mizuki Akiyama from Nightcord at 25:00."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.40,0:09:55.36,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"ProSeka AfterTalk is a stream where we look back on the event while reading letters from all of you."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.36,0:09:59.88,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"This time, we're focusing on "Reaching Out to an Unraveling Tomorrow.""
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.88,0:10:03.18,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Did you all enjoy the story?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.18,0:10:07.64,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"The event just ended yesterday. How was it for everyone?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.64,0:10:08.39,Default,host,0,0,0,,What did you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.39,0:10:10.74,Default,host,0,0,0,,I hope you all enjoyed it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.74,0:10:18.26,Default,host,0,0,0,,It was a story where Mizuki really faced their future and thought about what they want to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.26,0:10:21.06,Default,host,0,0,0,,I think it was a very meaningful chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.06,0:10:32.94,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"For those of you at an age where you have to decide on your education or career path, parts of this story might have really hit home."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.94,0:10:36.24,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Also, AfterTalk had a mini-renewal in April."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.24,0:10:42.58,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"We've been collecting your messages in advance via the official ProSeka Discord and email."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.58,0:10:44.98,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Thank you so much to everyone who sent one in."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.98,0:10:49.20,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'll be reading some of your letters during the show,"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.20,0:10:50.52,Default,host,0,0,0,,so please look forward to that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.52,0:10:54.60,Default,host,0,0,0,,If you want to post your impressions of the event or this stream,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.60,0:10:59.62,Default,host,0,0,0,,please use the hashtag #ProSekaAfterTalk.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.62,0:11:04.48,Default,host,0,0,0,,I'm keeping an eye on the YouTube chat and I'll check the hashtag later too,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.48,0:11:07.92,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"so I'll try to pick out some interesting comments."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.48,0:11:19.04,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"There are more international comments than I expected! I can't find many in Japanese. "Your ribbon is cute," "Your hair matches Mizuki's...""
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.04,0:11:21.60,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"The stream is probably a bit delayed for you right now,"
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.60,0:11:24.38,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"but I see people mentioning my hair and outfit."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.38,0:11:28.88,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I tried to match the card illustration for today."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.88,0:11:32.44,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Well, I always try to, but I was especially conscious of it this time."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.44,0:11:33.36,Default,host,0,0,0,,Good evening! Hello everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.36,0:11:34.64,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Thank you all for being here."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.64,0:11:37.76,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Oh, someone said, "The story and the new song were so good I sobbed.""
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.36,0:11:39.68,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'll talk about the song later."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.68,0:11:43.72,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"When I saw it at home, I was like, "What is this?!""
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.72,0:11:45.34,Default,host,0,0,0,,In a good way! I was just stunned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.34,0:11:48.80,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I really felt the incredible effort the team put into it."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.24,0:11:50.76,Default,host,0,0,0,,Yes, exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.76,0:11:53.68,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"But we'll save that talk for later."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.68,0:11:59.96,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"So, let's dive right into the story of "Reaching Out to an Unraveling Tomorrow.""
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.96,0:12:00.61,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Here we go."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.61,0:12:04.30,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"We received letters about this story as well,"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.30,0:12:07.68,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"so I'd like to look back on the events while reading them."
Comment: 0,0:12:07.68,0:12:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,=== Corner: Fan Letter Corner ===
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.68,0:12:11.26,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"First, we have a letter from Kotori no Mama."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.26,0:12:12.60,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Hello, Hinata-san! Ko-Niigo!"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.60,0:12:13.40,Default,host,0,0,0,,Ko-Niigo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.40,0:12:16.02,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"My child and I enjoy playing ProSeka together."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.02,0:12:19.92,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Mizuki-chan's banner was incredibly cute, interesting, and moving."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.92,0:12:23.02,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Through their past experiences and interactions with those around them,"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.02,0:12:28.16,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'm glad we got to see so many of Mizuki-chan's different feelings."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.40,0:12:36.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I think staying true to yourself and not giving up on what you love can be hard when you face obstacles."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.46,0:12:41.80,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"But I believe that if you hold onto those feelings, a time will come when they are rewarded."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.40,0:12:46.44,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Just like the members of Niigo, there are definitely people out there"
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.44,0:12:49.96,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"who will see and accept you for who you truly are."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.96,0:12:52.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I really love the stories in ProSeka."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.46,0:12:55.74,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Hinata-san, thank you so much for always voicing them."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.74,0:12:59.72,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'll continue to support both you and Mizuki-chan with all my heart."
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.72,0:13:02.08,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Thank you so much, Kotori no Mama."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.08,0:13:07.76,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"In this story, Mizuki's sister comes home from abroad."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.76,0:13:19.70,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It starts with the pop-up shop, and I felt it was a huge step forward for Mizuki to want their sister to meet the rest of Niigo."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.70,0:13:25.06,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Kanade and Mafuyu had met Yuuki-san before,"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.06,0:13:28.76,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"but Ena met her for the first time here. The story really progressed in many ways."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.28,0:13:31.66,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"There was a lot of development."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.66,0:13:38.80,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Mizuki loves making videos, but they also love things like"
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.80,0:13:46.96,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"remaking clothes, visiting boutiques, and looking at makeup. They have so many things they love."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.96,0:13:52.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"So, when it comes to what they want to do in the future, thinking about what they want to aim for..."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.46,0:13:56.76,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I think it's amazing that they're already facing those questions at this stage."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.76,0:14:00.48,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"When I was going to college, I just thought that if I was paying for it,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.48,0:14:08.74,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I had to study something that would give me a practical skill. I spent all my time at open campuses thinking like that."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.74,0:14:14.14,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"So, my approach to finding what I liked was completely different from Mizuki's."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.14,0:14:18.04,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Even so, I think this was a time for Mizuki to re-examine what they love,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.04,0:14:23.36,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"at their own pace. That's such an important thing to do."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.36,0:14:33.54,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It wasn't just about their sister's pop-up shop."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.54,0:14:42.49,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Being around those clothes helped them realize that it's not just a hobby—they might want to make it their career."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.49,0:14:49.30,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Realizing that is a huge deal, so I was just really happy to see them smiling."
Comment: 0,0:14:49.98,0:14:55.50,Default,,0,0,0,,=== Corner: Story Watchalong ===
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.98,0:14:55.50,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"All right, I've picked out some scenes that I personally wanted to talk about,"
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.50,0:14:57.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"so let's take a look at them together."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.46,0:14:58.22,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Here they are."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.80,0:24:51.40,Default,host,0,0,0,,Wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.80,0:24:53.62,Default,host,0,0,0,,Such a good story.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.62,0:24:55.04,Default,host,0,0,0,,It's a really good story.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.00,0:24:57.22,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"That's how I feel about it."
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.22,0:25:01.26,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Since I'm someone who has already chosen my own career path,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.26,0:25:04.36,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"witnessing the moment someone else makes a choice—"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.36,0:25:07.62,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"even if it's just through an event story—really resonates with me."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.62,0:25:18.60,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"There are always moments where you wonder if you're making the right choice. But if 10 or 20 years from now,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.60,0:25:24.76,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"you can look back and think, "I'm glad I made that choice back then," then it was definitely worth it."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.76,0:25:29.02,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I think that feeling comes from the effort you put in. When it comes to things that require hard work,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.02,0:25:35.76,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I don't think there's really a "right" or "wrong" choice."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.76,0:25:41.30,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"With a choice that involves real effort, you might think a year or two later,"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.30,0:25:44.68,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Oh, I shouldn't have done this."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.68,0:25:47.34,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"But looking at it over 10 or 20 years, I'm sure there are times"
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.34,0:25:50.52,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"where it all connects in the end."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.52,0:25:53.26,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"You'll think, "If I hadn't done that then, I wouldn't be able to do this now.""
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.26,0:25:56.48,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Even if you're in a different profession, I think you'll feel that way."
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.48,0:26:01.56,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"So for any kids out there who are working hard or have something they want to work toward, please keep at it."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.56,0:26:11.72,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I hope this event story serves as a catalyst for you to make that decision for yourself."
Comment: 0,0:26:12.48,0:26:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,=== Corner: Card Illustrations ===
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.48,0:26:16.76,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Now then, let's talk about the illustrations."
Comment: 0,0:26:16.76,0:26:18.68,Default,,0,0,0,,=== Corner: Fan Letter Corner ===
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.76,0:26:18.68,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"First, let me read a letter."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.68,0:26:21.48,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"This one is from Meshi-san. Thanks for writing in."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.48,0:26:23.38,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Thank you very much."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.38,0:26:25.58,Default,host,0,0,0,,"Hello, Sato-san. Kon-Niigo!"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.58,0:26:28.96,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'm always having fun playing ProSeka."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.96,0:26:34.88,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"The 4-star illustrations this time, especially Mizuki's, were so good that I went all out on the gacha to get them."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.88,0:26:38.97,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Just like the trained illustrations for 'Secret Distance' and 'Where Shall This Path Lead?',"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.97,0:26:39.50,Default,host,0,0,0,,"Where?"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.50,0:26:40.08,Default,host,0,0,0,,"Where Shall This Path Lead?"
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.60,0:26:44.32,Default,host,0,0,0,,"Mizuki was shown in a space filled with torsos."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.32,0:26:47.88,Default,host,0,0,0,,Torsos appear quite often in Mizuki's illustrations.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.88,0:26:52.00,Default,host,0,0,0,,They're like mannequins for displaying clothes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.00,0:26:55.96,Default,host,0,0,0,,Like the one right here... here... here... oh, here!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.96,0:26:57.00,Default,host,0,0,0,,Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.00,0:26:58.14,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"This is called a torso."
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.14,0:27:01.28,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It's the torso from "Reaching Out for an Unraveling Tomorrow.""
Dialogue: 0,0:27:01.80,0:27:04.70,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It was an illustration of Mizuki in a space with torsos."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.70,0:27:08.80,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Usually, the torso space represents Mizuki's dark feelings,"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.80,0:27:13.06,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"but this time, after feeling the warmth of family and friends, they're looking forward."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.06,0:27:17.16,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"The space now represents Mizuki's bright and cheerful feelings."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.16,0:27:20.40,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I was so happy to see this change in Mizuki's state of mind."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.40,0:27:25.16,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I can't thank the staff enough for creating such wonderful illustrations and scenarios,"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.16,0:27:29.24,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"and the voice actors for their amazing performances that bring such depth to the characters."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.24,0:27:32.44,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Thank you for always creating such wonderful events."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.44,0:27:35.08,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Please take care of yourselves and keep up the good work."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.08,0:27:36.68,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'll be rooting for you as a fellow Tofu."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.68,0:27:37.74,Default,host_meta,0,0,0,,That's what they wrote.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.74,0:27:39.94,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Thank you, Meshi-san."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.94,0:27:47.68,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Yeah, the colors in the illustrations are quite rare for Niigo, aren't they?"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.68,0:27:51.80,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"We've had pale colors before, but seeing Niigo bathed in sunlight..."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.80,0:27:54.04,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I mean, they don't go outside much to begin with,"
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.04,0:27:57.02,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"so seeing Niigo during the day felt very fresh to me."
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.02,0:28:01.28,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Usually, we don't see this kind of touch very often."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.28,0:28:05.72,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"But everyone's cards were great, not just Mizuki's—both before and after training."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.52,0:28:10.30,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It made me realize what amazing artists we have."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.30,0:28:13.04,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'm truly grateful. And actually,"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.04,0:28:18.42,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"we've received comments from the illustration team regarding the outfits this time,"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.42,0:28:21.28,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"so I'd like to share those as well."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.28,0:28:22.32,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Oh, there's a comment about it too."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.32,0:28:24.90,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Someone said, "Pure cuteness is rare, isn't it?""
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.90,0:28:29.06,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Mizuki, having been accepted by Niigo, wants to create clothes that can help children who have similar worries,"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.06,0:28:32.86,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"or children who can't bring themselves to like who they are."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.86,0:28:38.32,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Inspired by the story of Mizuki thinking about a future career in fashion,"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.32,0:28:44.38,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"we wanted to express the image of the future they're starting to envision—a future that's finally coming into view."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.38,0:28:48.92,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"So, we went with a simple and clean one-piece design with fewer gothic elements."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.44,0:28:53.70,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"As a special touch, we included the yellow daisy embroidery used in Mizuki's previous unit outfit."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.70,0:28:58.50,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"This carries the message of 'being true to yourself,'"
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.50,0:29:03.54,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"resulting in a simple outfit design that is uniquely Mizuki."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.54,0:29:08.40,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Also, to reflect the song's calm, warm impression and Mizuki's faint expectations for the future,"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.40,0:29:13.70,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"we used a palette of soft, gentle colors."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.70,0:29:14.96,Default,host_meta,0,0,0,,That's what they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.96,0:29:15.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.24,0:29:21.23,Default,host,0,0,0,,It's true that the colors are soft for everyone across the board.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.23,0:29:21.76,Default,host,0,0,0,,So that's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.76,0:29:25.00,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Did everyone notice the daisies? They're in there!"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.00,0:29:26.40,Default,host,0,0,0,,The daisies are there.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.40,0:29:28.76,Default,host,0,0,0,,Oh, I see people commenting "Daisy, daisy" now.
Comment: 0,0:29:28.76,0:29:29.47,Default,,0,0,0,,[autosub] Chunk boundary — review translation around this line
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.76,0:29:29.47,Default,host,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.09,0:29:30.67,Default,host,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.67,0:29:32.20,Default,host,0,0,0,,The blue traffic light was really striking.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.20,0:29:32.98,Default,host,0,0,0,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.98,0:29:37.54,Default,host,0,0,0,,And since Mizuki was born in summer, on August 27th... Happy Birthday!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.54,0:29:40.26,Default,host,0,0,0,,I didn't mean to say it so casually, but Happy Birthday to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.26,0:29:45.50,Default,host,0,0,0,,Even though they're a summer baby, I feel like they haven't had
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.50,0:29:47.48,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"that many summer-themed illustrations until now."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.04,0:29:54.64,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I always felt like they usually wore long sleeves or clothes that covered their skin,"
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.64,0:29:56.64,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"though they've had things like T-shirts before."
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.64,0:30:06.72,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"So I was really happy to see an illustration that feels so refreshing and screams "summer" the moment you look at it."
Comment: 0,0:30:06.72,0:30:13.26,Default,,0,0,0,,=== Corner: Card Illustrations ===
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.72,0:30:13.26,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"All right, then, let's talk about the event while looking at the card illustrations."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.86,0:30:16.66,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'm appearing on the monitor right now, right? On everyone's screens?"
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.54,0:30:19.54,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Yes, I'll believe that I am."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.06,0:30:23.38,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"First, let's look at Mizuki's pre-training card."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.02,0:30:24.54,Default,host,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.18,0:30:28.74,Default,host,0,0,0,,I absolutely love this illustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.90,0:30:36.26,Default,host,0,0,0,,First of all, seeing Ena looking at Mizuki with such a happy smile reminds me of the New Year's event,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.26,0:30:43.42,Default,host,0,0,0,,where Yuuki-san gave a ribbon to a young Mizuki. It really overlaps with that scene.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.42,0:30:48.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,And Mizuki's expression here, showing it off and asking "How is it?", is just incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.38,0:30:51.32,Default,host,0,0,0,,I can't believe this is just the pre-training art.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.32,0:30:52.38,Default,host,0,0,0,,Seriously.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.42,0:30:54.78,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I love the atmosphere of this space."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.78,0:30:57.26,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Apparently, that's a torii gate in the background."
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.26,0:30:59.90,Default,host,0,0,0,,All right, let's take a look at the post-training version too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.79,0:31:01.49,Default,host,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:01.49,0:31:02.26,Default,host,0,0,0,,So good.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.10,0:31:12.22,Default,host,0,0,0,,Butterflies and ribbons have always felt very symbolic for Mizuki,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:12.22,0:31:15.18,Default,host,0,0,0,,but in my mind, when those motifs appear in illustrations,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.18,0:31:17.66,Default,host,0,0,0,,I usually have a strong image of Mizuki holding scissors.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.66,0:31:29.82,Default,host,0,0,0,,But this time, there are no scissors. It's such a bright space, and even though their mouth is covered, you just know they're smiling. It's so precious.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.82,0:31:30.34,Default,host,0,0,0,,Really.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.34,0:31:33.38,Default,host,0,0,0,,My kid is such a good kid, honestly.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.38,0:31:35.74,Default,host,0,0,0,,Next up is Ena-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.50,0:31:39.60,Default,host,0,0,0,,I'm so happy Yuuki-san is here too.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.60,0:31:43.02,Default,host,0,0,0,,Meeting the older sister for the first time and being overwhelmed by how pushy she is...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.02,0:31:44.82,Default,host,0,0,0,,That "Whoa!" reaction from Ena is just great.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.82,0:31:46.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,Ena is just so good here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:47.74,0:31:49.02,Default,host,0,0,0,,Isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.02,0:31:54.22,Default,host,0,0,0,,If you haven't read the event story yet, please check it out in-game.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.22,0:31:59.10,Default,host,0,0,0,,Seeing the sister interact with all the siblings is definitely a must-see.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.94,0:32:03.34,Default,host,0,0,0,,Next... isn't this Ena amazing?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.42,0:32:07.76,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I've always thought girls with flowers in their hair look great,"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.76,0:32:10.18,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"so this illustration is incredibly good."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.18,0:32:12.06,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I almost thought she was a florist."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.70,0:32:13.44,Default,host,0,0,0,,Wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.44,0:32:14.36,Default,host,0,0,0,,Ena-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.36,0:32:15.10,Default,host,0,0,0,,So cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.30,0:32:19.20,Default,host,0,0,0,,The way she's looking down slightly is also very nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.20,0:32:20.54,Default,host,0,0,0,,Ena is just so cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.42,0:32:24.30,Default,host,0,0,0,,Next is Len-kun.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.30,0:32:29.82,Default,host,0,0,0,,How cute! Seeing him eating the souvenirs from his sister is just adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.82,0:32:31.34,Default,host,0,0,0,,Really cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.90,0:32:33.02,Default,host,0,0,0,,What is this level of cuteness?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.30,0:32:36.42,Default,host,0,0,0,,Even if that were a protein bar, he'd still be cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.94,0:32:38.30,Default,host,0,0,0,,I just want him to be eating something forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.30,0:32:38.82,Default,host,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.74,0:32:41.34,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Next is the post-training version."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.06,0:32:43.38,Default,host,0,0,0,,Isn't this insane?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.38,0:32:44.86,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I thought it was insane."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.74,0:32:46.84,Default,host,0,0,0,,Only you could pull this off.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.84,0:32:48.92,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I thought, "Wow, he really suits short pants.""
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.92,0:32:50.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,Truly beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.17,0:32:51.67,Default,host,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.22,0:32:53.18,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I just felt so thankful."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.58,0:32:57.22,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"The overall taste is quite rare for Niigo, which is nice."
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.22,0:33:01.34,Default,host,0,0,0,,Is he holding a book about daisies?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.34,0:33:01.84,Default,host,0,0,0,,Probably.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.62,0:33:08.94,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"My knowledge of daisies is a bit shallow, but I'm pretty sure that's what it is."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.86,0:33:10.72,Default,host,0,0,0,,Yeah, it's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.72,0:33:13.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,The idea of "sharing delicious things" is so lovely.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.46,0:33:14.74,Default,host,0,0,0,,Everything tastes better when you share it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.38,0:33:16.90,Default,host,0,0,0,,And then, there's this.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.30,0:33:18.90,Default,host,0,0,0,,Kanade-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.62,0:33:21.42,Default,host,0,0,0,,Way too cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.94,0:33:26.94,Default,host,0,0,0,,These clothes look exactly like something Mizuki or Yuuki-san would pick out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.94,0:33:27.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,Especially around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.26,0:33:29.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,She looks a little troubled too.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.46,0:33:31.02,Default,host,0,0,0,,Of course it suits her!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.02,0:33:33.08,Default,host,0,0,0,,Setting aside where she'd actually wear this...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.08,0:33:33.94,Default,host,0,0,0,,I mean, it's Kanade.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.94,0:33:39.38,Default,host,0,0,0,,I'm not sure if she'd actually wear that headpiece when she occasionally goes out.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.38,0:33:40.40,Default,host,0,0,0,,But it suits her.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.40,0:33:43.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"If it looks good, I think she should wear it."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.46,0:33:45.34,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Wow, she's really cute."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.86,0:33:47.42,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Thanks for always being so cute, everyone."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.58,0:33:49.66,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"And here's the post-training version."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.94,0:33:54.10,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"She looks like a proper young lady from a good family."
Dialogue: 0,0:33:54.10,0:33:56.28,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Are these daisies too?"
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.28,0:34:00.86,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"The ones on her chest and head probably are."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.26,0:34:12.98,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"In the side story, Kanade-chan is so cute being made to try on all these different clothes, so please check that out too."
Comment: 0,0:34:13.86,0:34:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,[autosub] Chunk boundary — review translation around this line
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.86,0:34:15.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Everyone's saying how cute they are."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.46,0:34:16.50,Default,host,0,0,0,,They really are adorable.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.26,0:34:18.18,Default,host,0,0,0,,Aren't they great?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.26,0:34:22.66,Default,host,0,0,0,,It really hits home how rare it is to see Niigo wearing white.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.66,0:34:24.98,Default,host,0,0,0,,Having done so many of these AfterTalks now...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.62,0:34:26.66,Default,host,0,0,0,,Mafuyu-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.66,0:34:29.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,Man, I have to say,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.82,0:34:33.26,Default,host,0,0,0,,it might not be a full-on smile,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.06,0:34:37.34,Default,host,0,0,0,,but seeing a version of Mafuyu with so much warmth makes me so happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.38,0:34:42.40,Default,host,0,0,0,,Because the event story itself was so heartwarming,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.40,0:34:51.86,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I think it's wonderful how all the illustrations have this gentle warmth to them."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.86,0:34:52.78,Default,host,0,0,0,,Just wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.78,0:34:54.18,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Thank you so much."
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.70,0:34:56.82,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"And that wraps up our card illustration segment."
Comment: 0,0:34:56.82,0:34:59.62,Default,,0,0,0,,=== Corner: Song Watchalong ===
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.82,0:34:59.62,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Next, we're going to talk about the new song written for this event by Onuma Parsley,"
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.62,0:35:07.44,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,""Envy Baby," while we watch the 3DMV together."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.44,0:35:10.12,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"But before we watch the 3DMV, I actually have a comment"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.12,0:35:14.42,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"from the Sega 3DMV production team to share with you all."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.42,0:35:24.98,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"In the 3DMV for 'Envy Baby,' we used the visual of falling underwater to represent Mizuki's wavering emotions and the feelings they can't quite express to the other members."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.98,0:35:29.84,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,""We utilized the insert feature and dedicated a lot of time to the underwater falling sequence,"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.84,0:35:32.50,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"going through a lot of trial and error to get the expression just right.""
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.50,0:35:36.20,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,""While we still face challenges in fully depicting a character's inner psyche,"
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.20,0:35:40.00,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"we hope you enjoy this new style of expression through Mizuki.""
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.00,0:35:40.70,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"That's what they had to say."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.70,0:35:43.61,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Now then, let's take a look at the 3DMV right away."
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.61,0:35:44.25,Default,host,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.36,0:37:58.64,Default,host,0,0,0,,Did you see that expression just now?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.88,0:38:00.72,Default,host,0,0,0,,They were smiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.76,0:38:02.98,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It's so good."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.98,0:38:03.96,Default,host,0,0,0,,Wow, that was wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.96,0:38:08.60,Default,host,0,0,0,,Honestly, I was blown away when I first saw the MV for "Consilium."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.24,0:38:13.22,Default,host,0,0,0,,I was like, "I can't believe the scenery changes this much!"
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.22,0:38:20.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,Like, it goes from a school-like setting to an after-school vibe, with shots through windows showing leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.46,0:38:24.88,Default,host,0,0,0,,And when they're walking down the hallway, you see those little things floating in the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.88,0:38:26.12,Default,host,0,0,0,,No, it's not Wi-Fi signals.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.12,0:38:27.50,Default,host,0,0,0,,What would you call it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.50,0:38:29.86,Default,host,0,0,0,,Like, not exactly dust, but you can see little particles in the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.86,0:38:33.92,Default,host,0,0,0,,The direction is so detailed, I kept wondering how they even did that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.52,0:38:36.22,Default,host,0,0,0,,It was really, really amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:36.22,0:38:45.60,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"And the way everyone spins around and the characters swap out... the direction was just incredible."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.16,0:38:47.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I loved it."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.46,0:38:49.28,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It's great that we can look back at it like this."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.44,0:38:54.86,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It's so good, and the 2DMV is also fantastic, so I want you all to see that too."
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.86,0:38:55.88,Default,host,0,0,0,,Regarding the 2DMV...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.76,0:38:59.04,Default,host,0,0,0,,Well, this is just my personal take,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.04,0:39:02.28,Default,host,0,0,0,,and since it hasn't been officially stated, I'm not entirely sure, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.28,0:39:08.24,Default,host,0,0,0,,In the 2DMV, Mizuki is sitting at a table with a cake, like a birthday seat,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.24,0:39:12.08,Default,host,0,0,0,,and the camera pans across things that symbolize Mizuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.08,0:39:16.90,Default,host,0,0,0,,You see things like the letter from their sister, clothes,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.90,0:39:19.32,Default,host,0,0,0,,ribbons, and stuff like that appearing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.04,0:39:21.88,Default,host,0,0,0,,The 2D version was really lovely too.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.92,0:39:24.10,Default,host,0,0,0,,Both were amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.10,0:39:25.92,Default,host,0,0,0,,I was surprised by how much information was packed in there.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.92,0:39:35.60,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Also, about the song... I feel like Mizuki's songs usually have a lot of painful lyrics."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.60,0:39:46.40,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I'm not trying to compare it to past songs, but I felt this one had a lot of very positive lyrics."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.40,0:39:57.44,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Even so, I still feel like Mizuki hasn't fully opened up yet, and there are still swirling emotions inside."
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.44,0:40:02.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"So, I consulted with the director about the nuances, like how much weakness"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.46,0:40:09.56,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"or strength we should add or subtract. We talked a lot while creating this song."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.56,0:40:15.28,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"For the parts that sound like a radio broadcast,"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.00,0:40:21.28,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"we discussed whether to put a lot of emotion into it or try making the voice a bit raspy."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.28,0:40:26.34,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"We consulted on many of those subtle nuances for this track."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.34,0:40:35.10,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I hope you enjoy both the full 2DMV and the 3DMV where Mizuki smiles at you."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.10,0:40:38.88,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Both are already uploaded to the official ProSeka YouTube channel,"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.88,0:40:41.88,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"so please go check them out."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.52,0:40:46.04,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Well then, although it was a short time,"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.04,0:40:51.56,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"this concludes the ProSeka AfterTalk for the "Reaching Out to an Unending Tomorrow" edition."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.56,0:40:54.18,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"To everyone watching the stream, how did you like it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.18,0:40:55.56,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Let me take a look at the comments for a bit."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.67,0:40:57.26,Default,host,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:57.26,0:41:01.46,Default,host,0,0,0,,"The atmosphere of Oonuma Parsley-san's MV and Niigo's 2D version were different, but both were great."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.46,0:41:02.24,Default,host,0,0,0,,That's so true.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:02.24,0:41:05.36,Default,host,0,0,0,,For Mizuki, how should I put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:06.08,0:41:12.02,Default,host,0,0,0,,Well, students have their career paths, and ProSeka is about to reach its 5th anniversary.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:12.02,0:41:17.20,Default,host,0,0,0,,Mizuki has been through a lot leading up to the 5th anniversary, but they're looking forward now.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.20,0:41:19.26,Default,host,0,0,0,,It shows that this happened, which allowed them to look forward,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.26,0:41:24.24,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"and that feeling of "I'm going to do my best" is summarized there."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.24,0:41:27.60,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I think the Niigo version feels like it's decorated with those feelings."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.60,0:41:29.74,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"As for Oonuma-san's version, how should I describe it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.74,0:41:37.10,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It's like an MV where a tired working adult is encouraging themselves to keep going and look ahead."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.10,0:41:51.56,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I felt that "Consilium" is a song with a very wide range depending on the singer and how it's expressed."
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.08,0:41:55.72,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"So please, check out Oonuma-san's... would you call it a 2D version?"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.72,0:41:56.56,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"What would you call that?"
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.56,0:41:57.94,Default,host,0,0,0,,The music video?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.94,0:42:02.42,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I hope you enjoy that MV as well."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.42,0:42:14.50,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Looking back at the event story, Niigo stories have often been heavy or focused on suffocating situations."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.50,0:42:23.32,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"But I think this story is one that high schoolers—from first to third years—"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.32,0:42:25.60,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"can really relate to on a personal level."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.60,0:42:35.74,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It's an event story that feels very true to life."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.74,0:42:52.70,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Whether it's deciding on a career path, or lacking confidence in your own interests... if there's anyone who feels they can't love what they like right now,"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.70,0:42:57.32,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"and that goes for working adults too, not just students... if you haven't seen the story or heard the song yet,"
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.32,0:43:05.12,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I think you'll find words that resonate with you exactly because of who you are right now."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.12,0:43:12.58,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"So, I hope everyone, both adults and students, enjoys it to the very end."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.42,0:43:25.86,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"If you haven't finished the story for "Reaching Out to an Unending Tomorrow," you can read it all from the event story archive once the next event starts."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.86,0:43:30.12,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"It will probably be uploaded to YouTube at a later date as well,"
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.12,0:43:31.98,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"so it's perfectly fine to wait for that."
Comment: 0,0:43:32.50,0:43:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,=== Corner: Fan Letter Corner ===
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.50,0:43:35.64,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"AfterTalk is always looking for your messages."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.64,0:43:40.96,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"You can submit them through the AfterTalk submission channel on the official ProSeka Discord,"
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.96,0:43:43.72,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"or via email."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.72,0:43:47.82,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Please send them in once the next AfterTalk event begins."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.82,0:43:51.68,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"We look forward to your messages regarding the event."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.68,0:43:59.08,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Well, August is almost over, and once September passes, the Thanksgiving festival awaits."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.08,0:44:02.62,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"We've been busy making preparations here and there,"
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.62,0:44:06.60,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"so I'd be happy if you look forward to that too."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.60,0:44:08.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"August is ending, but..."
Comment: 0,0:44:09.18,0:44:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,[autosub] Chunk boundary — review translation around this line
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.18,0:44:13.92,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"The heat isn't letting up yet, so please be careful not to get heatstroke."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.92,0:44:17.14,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"If you feel like it's too much, please don't hesitate to get away from it."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.14,0:44:18.54,Default,host,0,0,0,,Let's all escape the heat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.54,0:44:20.46,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Moving forward is what matters most."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.46,0:44:23.78,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"I hope to see you all at the Thanksgiving festival."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.78,0:44:25.96,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"We'll be waiting for you, whether you're watching the stream or at the venue."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:25.96,0:44:28.50,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Thank you so much for watching until the very end."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.50,0:44:32.42,Default,listener_mail,0,0,0,,"Let's survive this summer together, and I'll see you all again soon."
Dialogue: 0,0:44:32.42,0:44:34.56,Default,host,0,0,0,,Goodbye.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.56,0:44:35.34,Default,host,0,0,0,,Bye-bye!
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.45,0:44:50.95,Default,host,0,0,0,,Mafuyu Asahina.
